docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Impeachment was always going to hang heavily over a divided Washington. headline.print_headline: Cry to Impeach  Upsets Agenda For Democrats

docs.lead_paragraph: President Trump, the first president to rely on social media as a primary means of communicating with the public, has elevated early-morning tweeting to a veritable art form. His musings in bursts of 280 characters or less — often littered with misleading material, nods to conspiracy theories or downright falsehoods — have become a fixture of American life, driving cable news coverage and punctuating the political discourse.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump is considering taking executive action to bar migrants, including asylum seekers, from entering the country at the southern border, according to people familiar with the plan.
